Netizen contribution
The Jiangsu Communist Youth League announced the reason why Sony China's official Weibo was banned:
Suspected of alluding to the Korean War martyr Qiu Shaoyun
On October 12, Sony China posted a photo on Weibo with the caption "When the mountain flowers are in full bloom, she is smiling in the bushes."
Some netizens pointed out that October 12 was the day Qiu Shaoyun died, and the composition and form of the picture suspected of alluding to the martyr Qiu Shaoyun.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: In the article, the Jiangsu Communist Youth League emphasized that the acts of smearing, slandering, denying and overthrowing our national heroes are in a sense "digging up our ancestral graves."
